WEBVTT

00:04.738 --> 00:05.706 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Good evening.

00:05.739 --> 00:07.608 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
I'm Judy Woodruff.

00:07.641 --> 00:11.712 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
On the "NewsHour" tonight: The
Trump administration
outlines an aggressive plan to
crack down

00:11.745 --> 00:16.316 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
on undocumented immigrants and
to strengthen
border security.

00:16.350 --> 00:22.756 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Then, betting on Trump -- our
new series kicks
off in coal country, where
families are banking

00:22.789 --> 00:25.325 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
on the president's promise to
bring back jobs.

00:25.359 --> 00:29.563 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
DAKOTA HALL, Coal Miner: The
only thing that
I have really given thought
about is Trump

00:29.596 --> 00:32.332 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
getting in office and going back
to work.

00:32.366 --> 00:37.104 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
My American dream would just be
to watch my
kids grow up happy and healthy.

00:37.137 --> 00:42.075 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: And taking deep
breaths to
get through the school day --
how students

00:42.109 --> 00:45.279 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
in Baltimore are using
meditation to relieve
stress.

00:45.312 --> 00:49.383 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
CARLILLIAN THOMPSON, Principal,
Coleman Elementary
School: The children are now
able to embrace

00:49.416 --> 00:52.019 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
it and realize that: I don't
have to be angry.

00:52.052 --> 00:53.387 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
I don't have to fight.

00:53.420 --> 00:55.022 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
I don't have to show off.

00:55.055 --> 00:56.490 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
All I need to do is breathe.

00:56.523 --> 00:58.659 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: All that and more
on tonight's
"PBS NewsHour."

00:58.692 --> 00:59.660 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
(BREAK)

00:59.693 --> 01:12.472 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
JUDY WOODRUFF: The

01:12.506 --> 01:17.678 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
federal government has formally
begun moving
to get tougher on illegal
immigration.

01:17.711 --> 01:24.251 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The Department of Homeland
Security set that
in motion today with top-level
memos.

01:24.284 --> 01:28.822 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The new memos on immigration
were set in motion
just after President Trump's
inauguration.

01:28.855 --> 01:32.826 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
DONALD TRUMP, President of the
United States:
I just signed two executive
orders that will

01:32.859 --> 01:40.267 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
save thousands of lives,
millions of jobs,
and billions and billions of
dollars.

01:40.300 --> 01:46.340 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Now the secretary
of homeland
security, John Kelly, is putting
the presidential

01:46.373 --> 01:48.875 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
orders into practice.

01:48.909 --> 01:54.948 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
His directives greatly expand
the pool of
immigrants subject to quick
deportation.

01:54.982 --> 02:01.722 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Now anyone in the U.S. illegally
who's charged
or convicted of any crime is an
enforcement

02:01.755 --> 02:03.657 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
priority.

02:03.690 --> 02:08.628 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The Obama administration focused
on immigrants
convicted of serious crimes,
threats to national

02:08.662 --> 02:12.299 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
security and recent border
crossers.

02:12.332 --> 02:14.067 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
White House spokesman Sean
Spicer:

02:14.101 --> 02:17.104 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
SEAN SPICER, White House Press
Secretary:
The message from this White
House and from

02:17.137 --> 02:22.476 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
the DHS is that those people who
are in this
country and pose a threat to our
public safety

02:22.509 --> 02:27.014 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
or have committed a crime will
be the first
to go, and we will be
aggressively making

02:27.047 --> 02:28.882 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
sure that that occurs.

02:28.915 --> 02:34.087 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
JUDY WOODRUFF: The new
directives do not change
the Obama program known as DACA
that protected

02:34.121 --> 02:40.894 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
from deportation more than
750,000 young immigrants,
the so-called dreamers.

02:40.927 --> 02:45.499 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Mr. Trump addressed their plight
during last
week's White House news
conference.

02:45.532 --> 02:47.667 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
DONALD TRUMP: We're going to
show great heart.

02:47.701 --> 02:51.505 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
DACA is a very, very difficult
subject for
me, I will tell you.

02:51.538 --> 02:55.442 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
To me, it's one of the most
difficult subjects
I have, because you have these
incredible

02:55.475 --> 02:57.277 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
kids.

02:57.310 --> 03:02.115 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Today, he told
NBC News, "We
are going to try to take care of
the dreamers

03:02.149 --> 03:04.051 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
very, very much."

03:04.084 --> 03:10.290 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Authorities do plan to enforce a
longstanding
provision on people caught in
the act of illegally

03:10.323 --> 03:12.325 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
crossing the Mexican border.

03:12.359 --> 03:17.230 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
They will be sent back to
Mexico, even if
they're from a different
country.

03:17.264 --> 03:24.638 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
On plans for a border wall, the
Kelly memos
identify locations near El Paso,
Texas; Tucson,

03:24.671 --> 03:28.942 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
Arizona; and El Centro,
California, for initial
construction.

03:28.975 --> 03:34.815 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
In addition, Secretary Kelly has
directed
Immigration and Customs
Enforcement to hire

03:34.848 --> 03:40.720 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
10,000 additional officers and
agents.

03:40.754 --> 03:46.626 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
All of this comes amid rising
fears among
immigrants and nationwide
protests.

03:46.660 --> 03:51.264 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Last week, activists staged a
day without
immigrants, shutting down
restaurants and

03:51.298 --> 03:56.103 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
stores to highlight the
contributions of workers
born outside the U.S.

03:56.136 --> 04:01.942 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
WOMAN: I think it's important to
show support
and to try to open their eyes
that we're not

04:01.975 --> 04:03.844 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
here to be criminals.

04:03.877 --> 04:10.650 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: And immigration
advocates point
to two cases, in Phoenix and
Seattle, in which

04:10.684 --> 04:17.224 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
people were detained despite
apparent protection
under President Obama's
policies.

04:17.257 --> 04:22.362 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
In the day's other news: The
death of a Mexican
teenager at the hands of a U.S.
Border Patrol

04:22.395 --> 04:25.098 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
agent reached the U.S. Supreme
Court.

04:25.132 --> 04:30.704 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
It happened in 2010, between El
Paso, Texas,
and Ciudad Juarez, Mexico.

04:30.737 --> 04:36.276 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The agent was on the American
side when he
fired at the boy on the Mexican
side.

04:36.309 --> 04:39.045 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Details of what preceded the
shooting are
in dispute.

04:39.079 --> 04:44.784 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The teen's family is seeking the
right to
sue the agent in U.S. federal
court.

04:44.818 --> 04:50.257 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
In Israel, a military court
sentenced Army
Sergeant Elor Azaria to a
year-and-a-half

04:50.290 --> 04:53.960 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
in prison for killing a wounded
Palestinian
attacker.

04:53.994 --> 04:59.533 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Diana Magnay of Independent
Television News
reports on the outcome in the
hotly debated

04:59.566 --> 05:01.334 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
case.

05:01.368 --> 05:06.640 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
DIANA MAGNAY: Grinning with
nerves perhaps
as he enters the courtroom and
still in the

05:06.673 --> 05:11.878 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
comfort of his mother's arms as
he awaits
sentencing, Sergeant Elor
Azaria, 11 months

05:11.912 --> 05:18.151 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
ago an unknown teenage army
medic, now a household
name and something of a hero to
many in Israel

05:18.185 --> 05:24.491 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
after a military trial which has
divided the
nation.

05:24.524 --> 05:29.829 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And the national anthem from his
supporters
once the sentence is handed
down, 18 months'

05:29.863 --> 05:35.135 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
jail time, one year on
probation, and a demotion
in rank, which his defense team
says they

05:35.168 --> 05:37.404 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
will appeal.

05:37.437 --> 05:42.008 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Rewind to March last year in the
town of Hebron
in the occupied West Bank.

05:42.042 --> 05:46.313 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
On the ground is a Palestinian
man called
Abdel Fattah al-Sharif.

05:46.346 --> 05:51.117 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Moments before, he and another
Palestinian
had stabbed and wounded an
Israeli soldier.

05:51.151 --> 05:52.752 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
The other man is dead.

05:52.786 --> 05:55.355 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Al-Sharif lies wounded and
seemingly harmless.

05:55.388 --> 06:02.429 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
None of the soldiers pay him
much attention,
except for one, 19-year-old Elor
Azaria.

06:02.462 --> 06:10.270 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
He cocks his gun, steps forward
and fires.

06:10.303 --> 06:14.808 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
In Hebron today, Al-Sharif's
family watched
as Azaria celebrated.

06:14.841 --> 06:19.379 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The prosecutor had asked for
three to five
years, but the sentence was less
than half

06:19.412 --> 06:25.285 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
that, the judge citing
mitigating circumstances,
that Hebron was hostile
territory and the

06:25.318 --> 06:28.388 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
suffering the Azaria family had
experienced
throughout the trial.

06:28.421 --> 06:31.591 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
YOUSRI AL-SHARIF, Father of
Abdel Fattah Al-Sharif
(through translator): Getting a
year-and-a-half

06:31.625 --> 06:32.592 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
is a joke.

06:32.626 --> 06:34.361 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
This is not a sentenced.

06:34.394 --> 06:37.964 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
If one of us killed an animal,
they would
put us in jail for God knows how
long.

06:37.998 --> 06:39.699 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
They're just making fun of us.

06:39.733 --> 06:45.338 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
DIANA MAGNAY: For Azaria's
supporters, he's
a victim, doing his duty by the
country in

06:45.372 --> 06:48.875 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
