government.

06:59.753 --> 07:01.288 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
I don't blame the army.

07:01.321 --> 07:03.056 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
I blame Bibi.

07:03.089 --> 07:06.993 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
DIANA MAGNAY: Bibi, Israel's
prime minister,
Benjamin Netanyahu, has gone
from backing

07:07.027 --> 07:11.031 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
the military on Azaria's case
for last month
asking for him to be pardoned.

07:11.064 --> 07:15.535 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
JUDY WOODRUFF: The prime
minister was out
of the country today, and had no
immediate

07:15.568 --> 07:17.203 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
comment on the sentence.

07:17.237 --> 07:20.507 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
There has been another migrant
tragedy in
the Mediterranean.

07:20.540 --> 07:25.979 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
