from it?

44:01.772 --> 44:02.807 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
LEMUEL LAROCHE: Yes.

44:02.840 --> 44:03.941 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
Yes.

44:03.975 --> 44:05.776 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
CHARLAYNE HUNTER-GAULT: What was
it that you
learned?

44:05.810 --> 44:09.514 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
LEMUEL LAROCHE: What I took from
that lesson
was more of a -- this is a game
that can really

44:09.547 --> 44:11.682 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
unify races.

44:11.716 --> 44:14.118 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
This is a game that can really
unify people.

44:14.151 --> 44:16.020 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Chess is such a metaphor for
life.

44:16.053 --> 44:20.858 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
When I teach chess, I try to
teach it from
the perspective of, how do you
take this game

44:20.892 --> 44:23.828 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
and correlate it with the real
world?

44:23.861 --> 44:28.699 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And when teaching children how
to play chess,
I try to teach them how to look
at the world

44:28.733 --> 44:29.967 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
different.

44:30.001 --> 44:32.370 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The same goes, when you give a
man fish, he
eats for a day.

44:32.403 --> 44:36.173 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
When you teach a man how to
fish, he eats
for a lifetime.

44:36.207 --> 44:38.075 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
I try to apply the same concept
with chess.

44:38.109 --> 44:41.412 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
DIONNE MCALLA, Chess Player: I
think more
critically.

44:41.445 --> 44:46.484 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
