kids together.

45:38.669 --> 45:44.709 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
That, in essence, force the
parents to come
together, and before we know it,
we have a

45:44.742 --> 45:46.877 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
community that is really
beginning to build
collectively.

45:46.911 --> 45:50.147 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
CHARLAYNE HUNTER-GAULT: And they
begin to
understand each other beyond
chess?

45:50.181 --> 45:51.849 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
LEMUEL LAROCHE: Indeed, because
that's important.

45:51.882 --> 45:55.653 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And, oftentimes, chess is just
used as the
hook to bring them to the table.

45:55.686 --> 46:01.192 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But, beyond chess, now that I
have a relationship
with you -- if I have been
programmed to see

46:01.225 --> 46:08.332 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
you as a criminal, as a thug, as
a racist,
chess is a way for you to have
that one-on-one

46:08.366 --> 46:14.805 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
interaction, and now I realize
that man what
-- who I thought was a thug just
beat me in

46:14.839 --> 46:16.607 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
chess.

46:16.641 --> 46:19.877 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MICHAEL MORRIS, Chess Player:
What this is
doing is helping me learn in
life that you

46:19.910 --> 46:21.712 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
think ahead and plan ahead
before you move.

46:21.746 --> 46:24.448 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
CHARLAYNE HUNTER-GAULT: What
happens when
the police play chess with these
kids?

46:24.482 --> 46:28.252 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
LEMUEL LAROCHE: To watch the
police officers
engage with youth in a game of
chess is -- to

46:28.285 --> 46:29.987 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
