46:30.021 --> 46:33.791 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
One is because, a lot of times,
the way we
have been programmed and
conditioned to see

46:33.824 --> 46:38.529 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
each other, kids have been
programmed to hate
the police, based on historical
mistrust,

46:38.562 --> 46:43.034 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
as well as relationships that
they have had
with parents, or if they have
seen a police

46:43.067 --> 46:44.535 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
officer incarcerate their
parents.

46:44.568 --> 46:47.872 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
So there is a negative
stereotype about police
officers in our community.

46:47.905 --> 46:53.744 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And, oftentimes, police officers
have been
programmed to see a lot of young
African-American

46:53.778 --> 46:57.415 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
youth as criminals because of
the things that
they have dealt with.

46:57.448 --> 47:01.919 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Engaging the kids with the
police officers
in a game of chess, it helps
both the youth,

47:01.952 --> 47:05.690 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
as well as police officers, to
break the stereotypes
that we have developed about
each other.

47:05.723 --> 47:07.591 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
CHARLAYNE HUNTER-GAULT: And you
get reactions
from...

47:07.625 --> 47:11.495 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
LEMUEL LAROCHE: Very positive
reactions, because,
one, the kid now recognizes he
has seen a

47:11.529 --> 47:12.930 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
police officer smile.

47:12.963 --> 47:15.266 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
There's positive socialization.

47:15.299 --> 47:17.234 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
People are beginning to engage
with each other.

47:17.268 --> 47:20.204 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The police officer is telling a
kid, man,
you beat me in chess.

47:20.237 --> 47:23.541 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
