48:15.926 --> 48:20.498 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
This is a conference that brings
policy-makers
in the room with kids that are
affected by

48:20.531 --> 48:21.766 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
policies.

48:21.799 --> 48:23.400 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
CHARLAYNE HUNTER-GAULT: But now
you're talking
about chess.

48:23.434 --> 48:25.669 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I want to talk about how you do
it if you
don't have chess as the
centerpiece?

48:25.703 --> 48:30.241 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
LEMUEL LAROCHE: I truly believe
that it is
important to try to reach them
at the youth,

48:30.274 --> 48:31.542 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
at the ground level.

48:31.575 --> 48:34.612 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
CHARLAYNE HUNTER-GAULT: Who has
to take the
lead?

48:34.645 --> 48:40.751 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
What kind of people do you think
need to get
engaged in this, and how do they
go about

48:40.785 --> 48:42.620 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
bringing this in?

48:42.653 --> 48:47.792 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
LEMUEL LAROCHE: If we begin to
look at things
as we are all small pieces of
the big puzzle,

48:47.825 --> 48:50.594 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
then that helps to make the
picture a lot
more clearer.

48:50.628 --> 48:56.267 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The great WEB Du Bois said that
the problem
with the 20th century is going
to be the problem

48:56.300 --> 48:58.169 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
with the color line.

48:58.202 --> 49:03.574 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And it's sad that, in the 21st
century, we
still find ways to erase that
color line or

49:03.607 --> 49:07.678 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
find a way to turn that line
into a circle,
where we can include everyone.

49:07.711 --> 49:13.484 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I'm optimistic because I see how
we engage
the youth on the ground.

49:13.517 --> 49:18.889 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I see what happens when we
engage little white
boys, little white girls, and,
you know, Asian

49:18.923 --> 49:19.890 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
and Hispanic.

49:19.924 --> 49:21.892 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
We bring the kids together.

49:21.926 --> 49:24.361 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
I see that type of engagement
that they have.

49:24.395 --> 49:26.530 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
I see the genuineness in it.

49:26.564 --> 49:32.469 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And I'm in a position that, when
I see parents,
the parents, the parroting of
the parents,

49:32.503 --> 49:36.006 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
when the kids are repeating what
they hear
from the parents.

49:36.040 --> 49:40.044 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Then it's an opportunity for me
to redirect
that concept, redirect that
thought.

49:40.077 --> 49:45.482 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
So, by engaging the youth on the
ground, having
them engage, talk to each other,
having them

49:45.516 --> 49:50.154 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
play with each -- socialize with
each other,
I believe that that is the one
way that we

49:50.187 --> 49:51.989 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
can erase it.

49:52.022 --> 49:56.126 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And it's about allowing those
who have been
programmed to see you a certain
way, or how

49:56.160 --> 50:00.998 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
we have been programmed to see
other people
certain ways, that we really
begin to have

50:01.031 --> 50:04.034 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
that genuine dialogue, that
genuine interaction.

50:04.068 --> 50:05.669 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And I try to do that through my
work.

50:05.703 --> 50:08.138 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
But I am very optimistic that it
can happen.

50:08.172 --> 50:10.341 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
It's tough, but it can happen.

50:10.374 --> 50:13.544 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
CHARLAYNE HUNTER-GAULT: Thank
you very much,
Lemuel LaRoche, for joining us.

50:13.577 --> 50:16.680 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
LEMUEL LAROCHE: Thank you so
much.

50:16.714 --> 50:23.187 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
It's an honor.

50:23.220 --> 50:32.663 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
