51:14.371 --> 51:18.309 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
So we started looking for the
next place.

51:18.342 --> 51:22.947 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
It turns out there are few
resources for the
middle class.

51:22.980 --> 51:28.986 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
We found palatial residences
like the one
I think of as villa grande with
wine tastings

51:29.019 --> 51:35.893 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
and white table dining, or villa
even more
grande with personal butlers and
architectural

51:35.926 --> 51:39.296 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
layouts named for Picasso and
Renoir.

51:39.330 --> 51:44.702 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
The Michelangelo was the size of
New Hampshire.

51:44.735 --> 51:48.072 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I started waking up in the
middle of the night
just to search the Web.

51:48.105 --> 51:52.776 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Just how much are kidneys going
for these
days?

51:52.810 --> 51:59.083 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
My parents had champagne taste,
but were on
a box wine budget, and the place
that we found

51:59.116 --> 52:00.784 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
